## Spring Boot Integration

This template is designed as a Spring Boot library that can be easily integrated into Spring applications:

### Auto-Configuration

The library provides Spring Boot auto-configuration for seamless integration:

```kotlin
// Auto-configuration is automatically applied when the library is on the classpath
@SpringBootApplication
class MyApplication

fun main(args: Array<String>) {
    runApplication<MyApplication>(*args)
}
```

### Configuration Properties

Configure the library through standard Spring Boot properties:

```yaml
# application.yml
gap:
  {{LibraryName}}:
    enabled: true
    # Additional configuration properties
```

### Starter Dependencies

Include the library as a starter dependency:

```kotlin
dependencies {
    implementation("io.pexa.gap:{{LibraryName}}:0.2.0-SNAPSHOT")
}
```

## OpenAPI Integration

The template includes OpenAPI code generation capabilities:

### Generating Code from OpenAPI Specs

```bash
# Generate API code from OpenAPI specifications
./gradlew openApiGenerate

# Generated code will be available in build/generated/openapi/
```

### OpenAPI Configuration

Configure OpenAPI generation in `build.gradle.kts`:

```kotlin
openApiGenerate {
    generatorName.set("kotlin-spring")
    inputSpec.set("$projectDir/src/main/resources/openapi/api.yaml")
    outputDir.set("$buildDir/generated/openapi")
    // Additional configuration...
}
```

## Version Management

The library uses semantic versioning managed by the GAP publishing plugin with the base version stored in `version.txt`:

### Current Version Strategy

- **Base Version**: `0.2` (from `version.txt`)
- **Development**: `0.2.0-SNAPSHOT` (local builds)
- **Release**: Set via CI/CD environment variables

### Version Commands

```bash
# Show current version
./gradlew properties | grep version

# Build with specific version
./gradlew build -Pversion=0.2.1

# Check version in CI/CD
echo $VERSION  # Set by CI/CD pipeline
```

## Testing Strategy

### Test Structure

- **Unit Tests**: `src/test/kotlin/` - Fast, isolated tests for individual components
- **Integration Tests**: `src/testIntegration/kotlin/` - Component integration tests with Testcontainers

### Running Tests

```bash
# Run unit tests only
./gradlew test

# Run integration tests only (requires Docker)
./gradlew testIntegration

# Run all tests with coverage
./gradlew test testIntegration jacocoTestReport

# View coverage report
open build/reports/jacoco/test/html/index.html
```

### Integration Testing with Testcontainers

The template includes integration tests that demonstrate:
- **Real Database Testing**: PostgreSQL container for realistic testing
- **Spring Boot Integration**: Full application context testing
- **Auto-configuration Verification**: Testing library auto-configuration
- **End-to-end Functionality**: Complete workflow testing

**Requirements for Integration Tests:**
- Docker installed and running
- Network access for pulling container images

### Test Configuration

The template includes comprehensive test configuration:

```kotlin
testing {
    suites {
        val test by getting(JvmTestSuite::class) {
            useJUnitJupiter()
            dependencies {
                implementation(platform("org.junit:junit-bom:5.10.1"))
                implementation("org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-test")
                implementation("org.mockito:mockito-core")
                implementation("org.assertj:assertj-core")
            }
        }
        
        val testIntegration by registering(JvmTestSuite::class) {
            // Integration test configuration
        }
    }
}
```

